    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of deciduous, fruit-bearing tree of North America, found in forest areas from Ontario to Florida and from the Dakotas to Texas. Valued for dense, close-grain wood and its gum, a water-soluble carbohydrate that has been used as a medium for watercolor paints.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
